<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE49FF9D6B8DD4BFFC89F58C" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE49FF9D6B8DD4BFFEBCF5D9" blockId="15.[151,1436,762,1755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE49FF9D6B8DD4BFFEA2F54E" bold="true" box="[198,330,1535,1561]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE49FF9D6A24D740FD83F54E" box="[367,619,1536,1561]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE49FF9D6A24D740FD83F54E" box="[367,619,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Monotagma remotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE49FF9D680AD740FC21F54E" box="[833,969,1536,1561]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagmatis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="haughtii">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE49FF9D680AD740FC21F54E" box="[833,969,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. haughtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in having caudate leaf apices (vs. acuminate), a shorter synflorescence peduncle (15–25 vs. 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE49FF9D6F7BD766FB47F517" box="[1072,1199,1574,1600]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="cm" value="50.5" valueMax="68.0" valueMin="33.0">33–68 cm</quantity>
), and a longer first synflorescence internode (8.5–12 vs. 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE49FF9D6917D70DFD00F530" box="[604,744,1613,1639]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="cm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.8 cm</quantity>
). It was collected and first identified as a new species by Helen Kennedy.
</paragraph>
